trans-unit.source: A collection of <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects that represent the rows of an <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable"></xref> control.
This class cannot be inherited.

Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> class to programmatically manage a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> objects that represent the rows in an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable> control.
This class is commonly used to add, remove, or modify the contents of a row in an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable> control.

An <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable> control contains a <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable.Rows%2A> property that represents a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> objects.
Each <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> represents an individual row in the table.

An <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> contains a <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow.Cells%2A> property that represents a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableCell> objects.
These objects, in turn, represent the individual cells of the table.

To retrieve an individual cell, first get the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object, representing the row containing the cell, from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable.Rows%2A> collection of the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTable> control.

You can then get the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableCell> object, representing the cell in the row, from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow.Cells%2A> collection of the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow>.
Appends the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> object to the end of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.
Use this method to add the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object to the end of an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection.
To insert an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> in the middle of the collection, use the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Insert%2A> method.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> to add to the collection.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.

Use this method to remove all <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> objects from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection and reset the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Count%2A> property to `0`.

Copies the items from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection to the specified <xref href="System.Array"></xref> object, starting at the specified index in the array.

Use this method to copy the contents of the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection into the specified <xref:System.Array?displayProperty=fullName> object, starting at the specified index in the array.
The `array` parameter must be a zero-based <xref:System.Array?displayProperty=fullName>.
A zero-based <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that receives the copied items from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
The first index in the specified array to receive the items.
Gets the number of <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.

Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Count%2A> property to determine the number of rows contained in the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Count%2A> property is commonly used when iterating through the collection to determine the upper bound.
The number of <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
The default value is `0`.

Returns an <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref>-implemented object that contains all <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.

Use this method to create an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator?displayProperty=fullName>-implemented object that can be iterated through to get each item in the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to get the current element in the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move to the next item in the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move the enumerator to the initial position.

You must call the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method after creating an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator?displayProperty=fullName>-implemented object, or after using the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move the enumerator to the first item in the collection.
Otherwise, the item represented by the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is undefined.

An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref>-implemented object that contains all <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
Adds an <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> object to the specified location in the collection.

Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Insert%2A> method to add the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object to an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection at the specified index.
If you simply want to append an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> to the end of the collection, use the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.Add%2A> method.
The location in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> at which to add the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> to add to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
Gets a value indicating whether the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection is read-only.
This property always returns `false` to indicate that the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection can be written to in all cases.
`false` in all cases.
Gets a value indicating whether access to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection is synchronized (thread safe).

This property is derived from <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> and is overridden to always return `false` to indicate that access to the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection is not synchronized (not thread safe).

For more information on the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection.IsSynchronized%2A> property, see the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.IsSynchronized%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property of the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> interface.
`false` in all cases, which indicates that access to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> is not synchronized (not thread safe).
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> object at the specified index from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.

Use this indexer to get an individual <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection at a specified index, using simple array notation.
The collection is zero-based; therefore, the first element in the collection contains an index value of `0`.
An ordinal index value that specifies the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> to return.
An <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> that represents a row contained in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
Removes the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> object from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.
Use this method to remove the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection.
If you specify an <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> that does not exist in the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection>, no item is removed from the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
Removes the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> object at the specified index from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.
Use this method to remove the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow> object at the specified index from the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> collection.
The index number is zero-based.
Therefore, the first item in the collection has an index value of `0`.
If you specify an index that is outside the range of index values, an exception is raised.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRow"></xref> to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref>.
The specified index is outside the range of index values in the collection.
Gets the object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection"></xref> collection.
The object returned in this implementation is the current instance of the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableRowCollection> class.

For more information on the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlTableCellCollection.SyncRoot%2A> property, see the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.SyncRoot%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property of the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> interface.
An object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection.
